re losing to mainstreaming and assimilation. Through interviews with older activists, it also responds to recent attacks on lesbian feminists who are being made to feel that they've hit their cultural expiration date.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aFeminismxHistoryxUnited States. 0aFeminismzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aLesbian culturexHistoryxUnited States. 0aLesbian culturezUnited StatesxHistory. 0aWomen's studiesxUnited StatesxUnited States. 0aWomen's studieszUnited States. 4aAmerican Studies : American Studies. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Lesbian / Gay Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Women's Studies. 4aHistory : American History. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / LGBT Studies / Lesbian Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2016z978311149098440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438461786423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438461786/original  a978-3-11-149098-4  SUNY Press eBook Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles